<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 91-16-08 - Door Reinforcement Available To Correct Failed Doors</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi911608" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>91-16-08</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 1991</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Door Reinforcement Available To Correct Failed Doors</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 3000/4000 and 7100/8100 and S-Series vehicles. An easily installed door
                    reinforcement is available to repair door failure damage in the hinge mount area. The reinforcement
                    could also be used to prevent door failures.
                </para>
                <para>Effective July 15, 1991, all doors produced at the Springfield Body Plant have an improved upper
                    hinge mounting area to prevent door breakage, and a change was made to the mirror mount to prevent
                    door skin cracking. The design changes were incorporated into the inner door structure and cannot be
                    retrofitted to existing doors in the field.
                </para>
                <para>Trucks produced after August 1, 1991, should have the new doors. Service Parts doors will be of
                    the new design.
                </para>
                <para>The following information describes the parts required and the installation of the
                    reinforcement.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
