        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116081">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116081" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9116081.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Door</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If inner door hinge mounting reinforcement is not cracked or bent, door removal may not be
                        necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Straighten hinge mounting reinforcement to dimension shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116082">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116082" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9116082.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Straighten Hinge Mounting</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install upper hinge reinforcement plate and hold in position with the two hinge mounting
                    bolts. Drill 3/16 inch holes and install the seven monobolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use pop rivets. Monobolts are required for structural strength.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install reinforcement plate for lower hinge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116083">Figure 3</hotlnk>), following Steps 2 and 3.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116083" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9116083.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Install Reinforcement Plate</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refinish with paint as required.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In order to save time and cost, most local paint jobbers have the ability to put the interior
                        paint color you will need in aerosol spray cans.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
